    <abstract>
      <t>This document describes the use of a well-known Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) community for blackholing at Internet Exchange Points (IXP). This well-known advisory transitive BGP community, namely BLACKHOLEIXP, allows an origin AS to specify through the route server that IXPs should blackhole a specific route.</t>
